<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-10-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-10-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="828" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d828">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/5420: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Viborg</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Imbrie</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Viborg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-10-18"><hi rend="italic">October 18,
                                1919</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received 9:36 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>119. Finnish General Staff officially communicates to representative of
                            Northwestern Government here that the White Forces have occupied
                            Petrograd. The White flag is flying from Kronstadt.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">Imbrie</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>